title: For Sale:  Smith &Wesson Model 46 .22 lr
postcontent: rare S&W Model 46 semi-automatic pistol in .22 lr. This gun, SN 938xx, was marketed as the utility version of the Model 41. The finish is a flat blue, it does not have the cocking indicator of M41sof the same period, the machining is not as detailed, the grips are of red nylon rather than the wood of the M41, etc. The slide and barrel of these guns can fit in the M41 frame, but not vice versa. The internals were identical and the guns shot as well. Only 4000 of the guns were made from 1959-1968 a number went to military shooting teams who had requested a more utilitarian version of the M41.

postcontent:
Polish PPS-43C semi auto pistol ATF approved incl. 3x35rd. magazines 
•Caliber: 7.62x25 mm TT

This pistol has been fired once and is like new condition

 Original Polish PPS-43C in a semi-auto version. 7.62x25 caliber, considered a pistol due to overall length. Comes with three - 35rd mags. The PPS-43C (Pistolet-Pulemet Sudaeva, model of 1943 = Sudaev SMG) was born as an answer to the need for a weapon that is more compact and mobile than the PPSh-41, then in use by the Soviet Army. The PPSh-41 was somewhat too long to be used by tank crews and mobile recon groups and paratroopers, so late in 1941, the Red Army issued a request for a new more compact sub machine gun (SMG). The designer Sudaev initially designed his new SMG in 1942, and it was adopted under the designation of PPS-42. The next year he refined the design, and this final model was designated as the PPS-43. This model was manufactured in significant numbers (nearly two million PPS-43 weapons were manufactured between 1943 and 1946). The PPS-43 is sometimes referred to as the best SMG of World War II. After WWII, it was widely exported to pro-Soviet regimes around the world, and widely copied. This historical firearm has been re-designed to shoot from a closed bolt position. The safety is located at the front of the trigger guard. The receiver and barrel shroud are made from stamped steel. The rear sight is an L-shaped flip type and is marked for 100 and 200 meters, the front sight is a fixed blade type. The barrel is equipped with a simple muzzle brake. This firearm is an ATF approved pistol. The stock has no function and is permanently fixed in its folded position.
